Weighted Gene Correlation Network Analysis

NPT Huynh

22 October 2021

Abstract

Data from previously published RNAseq (Osipovitch et al., 2019). This vignette describes the weighted gene correlation network analysis on bulk RNA-seq data. 
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library("DESeq2"))
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library("caret"))
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library("ggplot2"))
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library("WGCNA"))
options(stringsAsFactors = FALSE) # necessary

PART1: Data import

Read in data

Count matrix by sample can be downloaded from GSE184521

counts <- read.table("./data/RNA/GSE184521_RNA_RawCounts.txt")
sampleData <- data.frame(row.names=colnames(counts), condition = c(rep("CTR", 4), rep("HD", 5)))

Expression matrix for WGCNA

dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = counts, colData = sampleData, design= ~ condition)
## Warning in DESeqDataSet(se, design = design, ignoreRank): some variables in
## design formula are characters, converting to factors
dds <- DESeq(dds, parallel=FALSE)
## estimating size factors
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
# Transform for WGCNA 
vst <- varianceStabilizingTransformation(dds)
data <- assay(vst)
# Reduce the number of genes going to the correlation network to only those with median > 1 TPM per condition 
# TPM is pre-calculated by RSEM
tpm <- read.table("./data/RNA/deSeq2_TPM.txt")
tpm <- as.matrix(tpm)
med <- data.frame(row.names = row.names(tpm), G19 = rowMedians(tpm[, 1:4]), G20 = rowMedians(tpm[, 5:9]))
med$min <- apply(med, 1, min)
keep <- row.names(med)[which(med$min > 1)]

data <- data[keep, ]
mat <- t(data)

PART2: WGCNA

Correlation network and selection of soft thresholding power

s <- abs(cor(mat))
# Choose soft thresholding
powers <- c(c(1:10), seq(12, 20, 2))
sft <- pickSoftThreshold(mat, powerVector = powers, verbose = 5, networkType = "signed")

# Scale-free topology fit index as a function of the soft-thresholding power

  sft$fitIndices[, 1],
  -sign(sft$fitIndices[, 3]) * sft$fitIndices[, 2],
  xlab = "Soft Threshold (power)",
  ylab = "Scale Free Topology Model Fit,signed R^2",
  type = "n",
  main = paste("Scale independence")
)

Adjacency matrix

# Calculate adjacency matrix
beta <- 18
adj <- adjacency(mat, power = 18, type = "signed hybrid")
TOM <- TOMsimilarity(adj, TOMType = "signed")
## ..connectivity..
## ..matrix multiplication (system BLAS)..
## ..normalization..
## ..done.
dissTOM <- 1 - TOM

Gene clustering

geneTree <- hclust(as.dist(dissTOM), method = "average")
modules <-
  cutreeDynamic(
    dendro = geneTree,
    distM = dissTOM,
    deepSplit = 2,
    pamRespectsDendro = FALSE,
    minClusterSize = 50
  )
##  ..cutHeight not given, setting it to 0.997  ===>  99% of the (truncated) height range in dendro.
##  ..done.
moduleColors <- labels2colors(modules)
# Gene dendrogram depicting modules and their corresponding gene members 
plotDendroAndColors(
  geneTree,
  moduleColors,
  "Module Colors",
  dendroLabels = FALSE,
  hang = 0.01,
  addGuide = TRUE,
  guideHang = 0.05,
  main = "Cluster Dendrogram"
)

Merge highly similar modules

# Further merge modules whose eigengenes are highly correlated
MEDissThres = 0.4 # Correspond to a correlation of 0.6
MEList <- moduleEigengenes(mat, colors = moduleColors)
MEs <- MEList$eigengenes
MEDiss <- 1 - cor(MEs)
METree <- hclust(as.dist(MEDiss), method = "average")
plot(METree,
     main = "Clustering of module eigengenes",
     xlab = "",
     sub = "",
     cex = 0.5)
abline(h = MEDissThres, col = "red")

merge <-
  mergeCloseModules(mat, moduleColors, cutHeight = MEDissThres, verbose =
                      3)
##  mergeCloseModules: Merging modules whose distance is less than 0.4
##    multiSetMEs: Calculating module MEs.
##      Working on set 1 ...
##      moduleEigengenes: Calculating 109 module eigengenes in given set.
##    multiSetMEs: Calculating module MEs.
##      Working on set 1 ...
##      moduleEigengenes: Calculating 16 module eigengenes in given set.
##    multiSetMEs: Calculating module MEs.
##      Working on set 1 ...
##      moduleEigengenes: Calculating 9 module eigengenes in given set.
##    multiSetMEs: Calculating module MEs.
##      Working on set 1 ...
##      moduleEigengenes: Calculating 7 module eigengenes in given set.
##    Calculating new MEs...
##    multiSetMEs: Calculating module MEs.
##      Working on set 1 ...
##      moduleEigengenes: Calculating 7 module eigengenes in given set.
mergedColors <- merge$colors
mergedMEs <- merge$newMEs
plotDendroAndColors(
  geneTree,
  cbind(moduleColors, mergedColors),
  c("Dynamic Tree Cut", "Merged Dynamic"),
  dendroLabels = FALSE,
  hang = 0.01,
  addGuide = TRUE,
  guideHang = 0.05
)

moduleColors <- mergedColors
colorOrder <- c("grey", standardColors(50))
colorOrder <-
  match(moduleColors, colorOrder) - 1 # Because module 0 is reserved for genes that don't belong to any modules
